  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/ 160&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 4</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>baby plum&nbsp;tomatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put them in the oven to slow-roast until serving (approx. 30 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the&nbsp;<strong>conchiglie&nbsp;</strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong>&nbsp;salt</strong>&nbsp;and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the<strong>&nbsp;conchiglie</strong>&nbsp;for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the<strong>&nbsp;conchiglie</strong>, reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> of the&nbsp;<strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/943.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong>&nbsp;streaky bacon</strong>&nbsp;into small, bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat and once hot, add 2/3 of the <strong>chopped&nbsp;bacon</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 3-4 min or until crisped, then transfer to <strong>kitchen paper</strong> and set aside (keep the pan!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
